summary: This is a travel authorization notification from the DOJ's E2 Solutions system, approving travel for an individual to conduct witness interviews in Los Angeles for the case U.S. v. Epstein (R19NYS13842). The travel is scheduled for September 17-20, 2019, and is pending final authorization.

events.title: Scheduled Witness Interview Travel
events.description: Approved travel for DOJ personnel to Los Angeles, CA to conduct witness interviews for the U.S. v. Epstein case.

keyFacts: The document is a travel authorization (ID 10643456) for the case U.S. v. Epstein (docket R19NYS13842).
The purpose of the travel is to conduct witness interviews in Los Angeles, CA.
The travel was scheduled for September 17-20, 2019, and was approved on September 12, 2019.
The document originates from the DOJ's internal E2 Solutions travel system, indicating official government investigation activity.
The traveler's name is not disclosed in the provided text.
